    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-12T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-12T20:00:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 411.57N83/191a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-12T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5792. For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName>:</p>
                <p>5. <hi rend="italic">Norway</hi>. We think agreement with British for division of
                    Norwegian tonnage should be made before initiating suggested negotiations with
                    Norway.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Denmark</hi>. We think it improbable that Danish negotiations
                    can be protracted much longer without complete rupture and if we are not to
                    proceed with these negotiations here to final conclusion without delay then we
                    think Danes should be frankly informed that negotiations are transferred to
                    London. War Trade Board.</p>
                <p>For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> from
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PFL1">Polk</persName>:</p>
                <p>In regard to above message feel it necessary that we should state to
                    representatives of Danish Government here that negotiations have been delayed
                    and transferred in compliance with wishes of French and British Governments.
                    This important in order to prevent this Government from being charged with bad
                    faith. Please cable your views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
